column2: b'@dividendblower Looks a win for $IAC too.'

b'With Vimeo, Turo, and MGM all now making big moves, we may look back at 2021 as a transformation year for $IAC and the beginning of something really really special. Very excited about their future.'
b"Turo is a fascinating and unusual investment for $IAC given their minority ownership. It has massive potential, but doesn't fit the offline to online framework that $IAC has mastered. 4/"

b"If Turo goes the SPAC route, I can't help but wonder if $IAC becomes involved in the PIPE. That will be extremely telling IMO. If they keep their ownership steady that would be a extremely bullish in my mind. 3/"

b"Then Turo announces they are planning to go public in 2021 via IPO or SPAC. Turo just turned a profit, making it a rare SPAC/IPO target. 2020 revenues are reported to be $153M. 10x revenue puts valuation at $1.5B, making $IAC's stake at $375M. 2/"
